author: geirm
msg: While TI is on, VM crashes when it attempts to define class which contains
method with absent local variable table information through JNI DefineClass.
When JVMTI is off, the local variable table of a class is not parsed, just skipped. When JVMTI is on, the local
variable table was parsed just fine. But the ambigous interface treated NULL returned by the parsing function as an
error, regardless of whether the local variable table was incorrect or just absent. Usually local variable table is
present, but classes are allowed not to have it. So when this table was just absent in a class, an error was returned
tested on ubuntu - smoke and c-unit passed
